“How you gonna name yourself after a damn gun/And have a man bun?” American rapper Eminem has finally responded to Machine Gun Kelly (MGK) with a new diss track called Killshot, a response to MGK’s Rap Devil. Read More: Machine Gun Kelly’s Diss Track To “Kamikaze” Is Getting Everyone’s Attention MGK’s response came after Eminem’s Not Alike on his recently-released album Kamikaze. Eminem rapping. Photo: Twitter Killshot has the rapper dropping lines like: “I’m 45 and I’m still outselling you.” He also responds directly to some of the claims on Rap Devil. In response to MGK’s “Last time you saw 8 Mile was at home on a treadmill, Em says, “I’m really sorry you want me to have a heart attack / Was watchin’ 8 Mile on my NordicTrack / Realised I forgot to call you back.” And that’s not all. Eminem also taunts MGK for eating cereal in the Rap Devil video, rapping, “The day you put out a hit’s the day Diddy admits that he put the hit out that got Pac killed.” At the end of the track, he says, “Oh, and I’m just playin’, Diddy. You know I love you.” Take a look at the song below and feel free to share your thoughts on it in the comments section: 